  "prompt": "How do I judge a person as a potential friend?",
  "response": "When assessing a potential friend, consider these factors:\n\n1. Character traits\n- Trustworthiness\n- Honesty\n- Reliability\n- Kindness\n- Empathy\n\n2. Communication\n- Good listening skills\n- Respectful dialogue\n- Ability to have meaningful conversations\n- Mutual understanding\n\n3. Shared interests\n- Common hobbies\n- Similar values\n- Compatible sense of humor\n- Mutual goals/passions\n\n4. Personal boundaries\n- Respects your space\n- Understands consent\n- Not manipulative\n- Supports your growth\n\n5. Positive interactions\n- Makes you feel comfortable\n- Brings positive energy\n- Supportive during challenges\n- Celebrates your successes\n\n6. Consistency\n- Dependable behavior\n- Follow-through on commitments\n- Stable emotional responses\n\n7. Red flags to watch for\n- Excessive negativity\n- Constant criticism\n- Manipulative behavior\n- Disrespect for your boundaries\n\n8. Intuition\n- Trust your gut feeling\n- Pay attention to how you feel around them\n- Notice if interactions feel genuine\n\nRemember, friendship develops gradually. Take time to know someone before fully committing to a close friendship.",
